<taxonomicName authority="Chernyshev, 1993" authorityName="Chernyshev" authorityYear="1993" box="[199,550,151,177]" class="Enopla" family="Oerstediidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Monostilifera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Nemertea" rank="family">
Oerstediidae 
<bibRefCitation author="Chernyshev, A. V." box="[348,550,151,177]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="11 - 20" refId="ref20729" refString="Chernyshev, A. V. (1993) A review of the genera of nemerteans allied to Oerstedia (Monostilifera, Tetrastemmatidae) with description of four new species. Zoologischeskii Zhurnal, 72, 11 - 20." type="journal article" year="1993">Chernyshev, 1993</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Gibson, 1990 a" authorityName="Gibson" authorityYear="1990" box="[604,972,151,177]" class="Enopla" family="Plectonemertidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Monostilifera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Nemertea" rank="family">
Plectonemertidae 
<bibRefCitation author="Gibson, R." box="[805,972,151,177]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" refId="ref24160" refString="Gibson, R. (1990 a) The macrobenthic nemertean fauna of Hong Kong. In: Morton, B. S. (Ed.), Proceedings of the Second International Marine Biological Workshop: The Marine Flora and Fauna of Hong Kong and Southern China. Vol. 1. Hong Kong University Press, Hong Kong, pp. 33 - 212." type="book" year="1990">Gibson, 1990a</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="158" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,217,604]" box="[151,249,217,243]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis box="[151,249,217,243]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,217,604]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">
As far as I am aware, 
<bibRefCitation author="Moore, J. &amp; Gibson, R." box="[439,710,253,280]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="75 - 86" refId="ref30674" refString="Moore, J. &amp; Gibson, R. (1988) Marine relatives of terrestrial nemerteans: the genus Prosadenoporus Burger, 1890 (Hoplonemertea). Hydrobiologia, 156, 75 - 86. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / BF 00027980" type="journal article" year="1988">Moore &amp; Gibson (1988)</bibRefCitation>
were the first to envisage 
<taxonomicName authority="Quatrefages, 1846" authorityName="Quatrefages" authorityYear="1846" box="[1000,1321,253,279]" class="Enopla" family="Oerstediidae" genus="Oerstedia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Monostilifera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Nemertea" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1000,1110,253,279]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Oerstedia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Quatrefages, A. de" box="[1117,1321,253,279]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="173 - 303" refId="ref31808" refString="Quatrefages, A. de (1846) Etude sur les types inferieurs de l'embrachement des anneles. Annales des Sciences Naturelles, Zoologie, Serie 3, 6, 173 - 303. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 47986  page / 179 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1846">Quatrefages, 1846</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
as closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gibson" authorityYear="1990" box="[262,456,289,315]" class="Enopla" family="Plectonemertidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Monostilifera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Nemertea" rank="family">Plectonemertidae</taxonomicName>
by having two vascular plugs. This conjecture was later confirmed with molecular phylogenetic analyses, first by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mateos, E. &amp; Giribet, G." box="[454,731,325,352]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="235 - 243" refId="ref30003" refString="Mateos, E. &amp; Giribet, G. (2008) Exploring the molecular diversity of terrestrial nemerteans (Hoplonemertea, Monostilifera, Acteonemertidae) in a continental landmass. Zoologica Scripta, 37, 235 - 243. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2008.00324. x" type="journal article" year="2008">Mateos &amp; Giribet (2008)</bibRefCitation>
and then more convincingly by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kajihara, H. &amp; Kuris, A." box="[1089,1365,325,351]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="1 - 15" refId="ref28316" refString="Kajihara, H. &amp; Kuris, A. (2013) Ovicides paralithodis (Nemertea, Carcinonemertidae), a new species of symbiotic egg predator of the red king crab Paralithodes camtchaticus (Tilesius, 1815) (Decapoda, Anomura). ZooKeys, 258, 1 - 15. http: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 258.4260" type="journal article" year="2013">Kajihara &amp; Kuris (2013)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kvist, S. &amp; Laumer, C. E. &amp; Junoy, J. &amp; Giribet, G." pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="287 - 308" refId="ref29216" refString="Kvist, S., Laumer, C. E., Junoy, J. &amp; Giribet, G. (2014) New insights into the phylogeny, systematics and DNA barcoding of Nemertea. Invertebrate Systematics, 28, 287 - 308. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / IS 13061" type="journal article" year="2014">
Kvist 
<emphasis box="[151,202,361,387]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">et al</emphasis>
. (2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kvist, S. &amp; Chernyshev, A. V. &amp; Giribet, G." box="[299,359,361,388]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="105 - 119" refId="ref29273" refString="Kvist, S., Chernyshev, A. V. &amp; Giribet, G. (2015) Phylogeny of Nemertea with special interest in the placement of diversity from Far East Russia and northeast Asia. Hydrobiologia, 760, 105 - 119. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10750 - 015 - 2310 - 5" type="journal article" year="2015">2015</bibRefCitation>
), and 
<bibRefCitation author="Chernyshev, A. V. &amp; Polyakova, N. E." box="[429,810,361,387]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="64 - 73" refId="ref21353" refString="Chernyshev, A. V. &amp; Polyakova, N. E. (2018 a) Nemerteans of the Vema-TRANSIT expedition: First data on diversity with description of two new genera and species. Deep-Sea Research, Part II, 148, 64 - 73. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. dsr 2.2017.06.004" type="journal article" year="2018">
Chernyshev &amp; Polyakova (2018 
<bibRefCitation author="Chernyshev, A. V. &amp; Polyakova, N. E." box="[797,810,361,387]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="102148" refId="ref21485" refString="Chernyshev, A. V. &amp; Polyakova, N. E. (2019) Nemerteans from the deep-sea expedition KuramBio II with descriptions of three new hoplonemerteans from the Kuril-Kamchatka Trench. Progress in Oceanography, 178, 102148. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. pocean. 2019.102148" type="journal article" year="2019">a</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, b, 2019) [
<taxonomicName authorityName="Quatrefages" authorityYear="1846" box="[936,1046,361,387]" class="Enopla" family="Oerstediidae" genus="Oerstedia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Monostilifera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Nemertea" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[936,1046,361,387]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Oerstedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not included in the extensive analysis by 
<bibRefCitation author="Andrade, S. C. S. &amp; Strand, M &amp; Schwartz, M. &amp; Chen, H. &amp; Kajihara, H. &amp; Sun, S. &amp; Junoy, J. &amp; Thiel, M. &amp; Norenburg, J. L. &amp; Turbeville, J. M. &amp; Giribet, G. &amp; Sundberg, P." box="[286,538,397,424]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="141 - 159" refId="ref19155" refString="Andrade, S. C. S., Strand, M, Schwartz, M., Chen, H., Kajihara, H., D Ë† hren, J. v., Sun, S., Junoy, J., Thiel, M., Norenburg, J. L., Turbeville, J. M., Giribet, G. &amp; Sundberg, P. (2012) Disentangling ribbon worm relationships: multi-locus analysis supports traditional classification on the phylum Nemertea. Cladistics, 28, 141 - 159. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 0031.2011.00376. x" type="journal article" year="2012">
Andrade 
<emphasis box="[391,442,397,423]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">et al</emphasis>
. (2012)
</bibRefCitation>
]. The clade comprising 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chernyshev" authorityYear="2005" box="[811,1002,397,423]" class="Enopla" family="Acteonemertidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Monostilifera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Nemertea" rank="family">Acteonemertidae</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Quatrefages" authorityYear="1846" box="[1036,1146,397,423]" class="Enopla" family="Oerstediidae" genus="Oerstedia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Monostilifera" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" phylum="Nemertea" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1036,1146,397,423]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="158">Oerstedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and their kin was named 
<taxonomicName box="[151,280,433,459]" class="Enopla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraOrder="Oerstediina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Monostilifera" pageId="7" pageNumber="157" phylum="Nemertea" rank="infraOrder">Oerstediina</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chernyshev, A. V. &amp; Polyakova, N. E." box="[294,650,433,459]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="102148" refId="ref21485" refString="Chernyshev, A. V. &amp; Polyakova, N. E. (2019) Nemerteans from the deep-sea expedition KuramBio II with descriptions of three new hoplonemerteans from the Kuril-Kamchatka Trench. Progress in Oceanography, 178, 102148. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. pocean. 2019.102148" type="journal article" year="2019">Chernyshev &amp; Polyakova 2019</bibRefCitation>
), with neither Linnaean rank nor morphological circumscription. Here I place it at the infraorder rank. The suffix -ina must be used for the name of a subtribe when the taxon is placed on any of family group ranks in accordance with Article 29.2 of the Code (ICZN 1999); however, the Code (ICZN 1999) does not forbid the usage of -ina for ranks above the family group. While this may lead to confusion, I leave the ending as it was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chernyshev, A. V. &amp; Polyakova, N. E." box="[524,896,577,603]" pageId="7" pageNumber="158" pagination="102148" refId="ref21485" refString="Chernyshev, A. V. &amp; Polyakova, N. E. (2019) Nemerteans from the deep-sea expedition KuramBio II with descriptions of three new hoplonemerteans from the Kuril-Kamchatka Trench. Progress in Oceanography, 178, 102148. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. pocean. 2019.102148" type="journal article" year="2019">Chernyshev &amp; Polyakova (2019)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
